article.headline: Sam Houston St. 30, Gardner-Webb 14
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- Brian Bell threw two touchdown passes and Miguel Antonio kicked three field goals as Sam Houston State defeated Gardner-Webb 30-14 on Saturday night. Bell, a true freshman, was 6 of 13 for 163 yards for the Bearkats (1-2). He threw scoring passes of 33 yards to Kevin Matthews and 60 yards to Richard Sincere during the second quarter, lifting Sam Houston State to a 24-7 halftime lead against the Runnin' Bulldogs (2-2). Tim Flanders had 104 yards and a touchdown on 19 rushes for the Bearkats. Jamal Patmon caught six passes for 124 yards and a touchdown for Gardner-Webb.
